goals.question: What is the distribution of income per capita across all regions?
goals.rationale: This visualization will show the median, quartiles, and outliers of the income per capita distribution, giving an idea of the spread and skewness of the data.

goals.question: What is the relationship between income per capita and total income?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of income_per_capita vs total
goals.rationale: This visualization will show if there is a correlation between income per capita and total income, which can help identify regions with high or low income per capita despite having similar total income.

goals.question: What is the income distribution for each income group?
goals.visualization: histogram of income_per_capita for each income group
goals.rationale: This visualization will show the shape of the income distribution for each income group, which can help identify which income groups have higher or lower income per capita.

goals.question: What is the distribution of percentage of total income for each region?
goals.visualization: bar chart of pct for each region
goals.rationale: This visualization will show the percentage of total income for each region, which can help identify which regions contribute the most to the total income.

goals.question: What is the distribution of income per capita for each region?
goals.visualization: box plot of income_per_capita for each region
goals.rationale: This visualization will show the median, quartiles, and outliers of the income per capita distribution for each region, which can help identify which regions have higher or lower income per capita compared to others.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.boxplot(x=data["income_per_capita"])
    plt.title("What is the distribution of income per capita across all regions?", wrap=True)
    chart.axvline(data["income_per_capita"].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data["income_per_capita"].median()))
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
